{"questionId":"3096991","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>This method of determining the cost was noticed by a mathematician, Kepler, who decided to try to calculate the dimensions of a barrel which would give the maximum volume of wine for a given length <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>SD</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>Initially he modelled the barrel as a cylinder, with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi></math> at the midpoint of one side. He took the length of the cylinder as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>h</mi></math> metres and its radius as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> metres, as shown in the following diagram of the cross-section.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong>diagram not to scale</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/20346867d628dea451f56f0e0b6b704a79e544d0.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find an expression for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt at using Pythagoras &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>r</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>)</mo></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"3096991","referenceCode":"23M.3.AHL.TZ1.1c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find an expression for r2 in terms of d and h.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.3—Angles of elevation and depression"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}